missions.title: Mercury-Redstone 3
missions.description: First human spaceflight in the Mercury program, also known as the Freedom 7 mission, piloted by Alan Shepard.

missions.title: Apollo 11
missions.description: First manned mission to land on the Moon, commanded by Neil Armstrong and piloted by Buzz Aldrin.

missions.title: Voyager 2
missions.description: Space probe launched by NASA to study the outer planets. Explored Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, and Neptune.

missions.title: Curiosity Rover
missions.description: Mars rover launched to explore the Gale Crater on Mars, part of NASA's Mars Science Laboratory mission.

missions.title: Hubble Space Telescope
missions.description: Space telescope launched into low Earth orbit in 1990, providing high-resolution images of celestial objects.

missions.title: New Horizons
missions.description: Space probe launched to study Pluto and the Kuiper Belt, providing valuable data about these distant regions.

missions.title: Mars 2020 Perseverance Rover
missions.description: Mars rover designed to explore the Martian surface and search for signs of past life.

missions.title: James Webb Space Telescope
missions.description: Upcoming space telescope aiming to succeed the Hubble Space Telescope, set to study the cosmos.

missions.title: Europa Clipper Mission
missions.description: Planned mission to explore Jupiter's moon Europa, assessing its potential for habitability.

missions.title: Artemis Program
missions.description: NASA's program aiming to return humans to the Moon and establish a sustainable presence there.
